  "prompt": "Are there any TV series similar to How to Get Away with Murder?",
  "response": "If you enjoyed \"How to Get Away with Murder,\" you might like these similar TV series that blend elements of legal drama, suspense, and complex characters:\n\n1. **Suits**\n   - A legal drama that follows a talented college dropout who talks his way into a job as an associate at a prestigious law firm.\n\n2. **Scandal**\n   - Created by Shonda Rhimes (the same creator as \"How to Get Away with Murder\"), this series follows a former White House Communications Director who starts her own crisis management firm.\n\n3. **The Good Wife**\n   - A legal and political drama about a woman who returns to her career in law after her husband's very public sex and political corruption scandal.\n\n4. **Damages**\n   - A legal thriller that focuses on the complex relationship between a young lawyer and her seasoned mentor as they take on high-profile cases.\n\n5. **Goliath**\n   - Follows a washed-up lawyer who has one last shot at redemption by taking on a case against a massive corporate foe.\n\n6. **The Night Of**\n   - A gripping miniseries that follows the ordeal of a young Pakistani-American man who is charged with murder after a night of partying.\n\n7. **Liar**\n   - A British thriller series that explores the aftermath of a seemingly innocent first date that goes awry, leading to accusations of sexual assault.\n\n8. **Defending Jacob**\n   - A limited series that follows an assistant district attorney whose son is accused of murder, forcing him to question everything he believes about his family.\n\n9. **Mindhunter**\n   - While more focused on criminal psychology, this series delves into the murky world of serial killers and the FBI agents who study them.\n\n10. **Killing Eve**\n    - A thrilling cat-and-mouse game between a British intelligence officer and a psychopathic assassin.\n\nThese shows share elements of suspense, legal maneuvering, and intricate character development that fans of \"How to Get Away with Murder\" might appreciate.",
